   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Medical Entity Extraction\\n\",\"**NLP Project 25 of 100** — Extract symptoms, drugs, and diagnoses from clinical notes using spaCy and pattern matching.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Apply NER to medical/clinical text.\\n\",\"2. Build domain-specific entity patterns.\\n\",\"3. Handle medical terminology and abbreviations.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['pandas','numpy','spacy','matplotlib','seaborn']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\ntry: import spacy; spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nexcept: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','spacy','download','en_core_web_sm'])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re, spacy\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nnlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Medical entity patterns\\nruler = nlp.add_pipe('entity_ruler', before='ner')\\npatterns = [\\n    {'label':'SYMPTOM','pattern':s} for s in ['fever','headache','cough','chest pain','fatigue',\\n     'nausea','dizziness','shortness of breath','back pain','insomnia','anxiety','depression']\\n] + [\\n    {'label':'DRUG','pattern':d} for d in ['ibuprofen','aspirin','metformin','lisinopril','omeprazole',\\n     'amoxicillin','acetaminophen','prednisone','atorvastatin','losartan','insulin']\\n] + [\\n    {'label':'DIAGNOSIS','pattern':d} for d in ['diabetes','hypertension','pneumonia','asthma',\\n     'bronchitis','arthritis','migraine','anemia','COPD','heart failure','COVID-19']\\n]\\nruler.add_patterns(patterns)\\nprint(f'Added {len(patterns)} medical patterns.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"clinical_notes = [\\n    'Patient presents with fever and cough for 3 days. Prescribed amoxicillin. Diagnosis: pneumonia.',\\n    'Chronic headache and fatigue. History of hypertension. Currently taking lisinopril and aspirin.',\\n    'Complaint of chest pain and shortness of breath. Rule out heart failure. Started on losartan.',\\n    'Type 2 diabetes management. A1C elevated. Adjusted metformin dosage. Patient reports nausea.',\\n    'Follow-up for asthma. Symptoms improved on prednisone. Occasional cough persists.',\\n]\\n\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\nfor note in clinical_notes:\\n    doc = nlp(note)\\n    entities = defaultdict(list)\\n    for ent in doc.ents:\\n        if ent.label_ in ('SYMPTOM','DRUG','DIAGNOSIS'):\\n            entities[ent.label_].append(ent.text)\\n    print(f'Note: {note[:60]}...')\\n    for label in ['SYMPTOM','DRUG','DIAGNOSIS']:\\n        if entities[label]: print(f'  {label}: {entities[label]}')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Aggregate entity counts\\nall_entities = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int))\\nfor note in clinical_notes:\\n    doc = nlp(note)\\n    for ent in doc.ents:\\n        if ent.label_ in ('SYMPTOM','DRUG','DIAGNOSIS'):\\n            all_entities[ent.label_][ent.text] += 1\\n\\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(15,4))\\nfor ax, label in zip(axes, ['SYMPTOM','DRUG','DIAGNOSIS']):\\n    counts = dict(sorted(all_entities[label].items(), key=lambda x:-x[1])[:8])\\n    ax.barh(list(counts.keys()), list(counts.values()), color='steelblue')\\n    ax.set_title(f'{label} Frequency'); ax.invert_yaxis()\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Rule-based NER effectively extracts medical entities** from structured clinical notes.\\n\",\"- **Domain-specific dictionaries are essential** — general NER misses medical terms.\\n\",\"- **For production, use biomedical NER models** (SciSpacy, BioBERT) trained on medical corpora.\\n\",\"- **HIPAA compliance** must be considered when processing real patient data.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
    " \"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.11.0\"}},\n",
